               <p> - GAZE. I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18290910-287-person2688">
                  Henry 
                  Gaze
               <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2688" type="surname" value="Gaze"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2688" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2688" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            : he <rs id="t18290910-287-viclabel1584" type="occupation">has a milliner's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-287-victim2687 t18290910-287-viclabel1584"></join> in <placeName id="t18290910-287-crimeloc1585">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-287-crimeloc1585" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-287-crimeloc1585" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-287-off1582 t18290910-287-crimeloc1585"></join>. The prisoner came there, and asked to look at some ribbons, at half-past five o'clock, on the 22nd of August; I shewed her some - she staid above five minutes; she did not buy any, but was going away - I saw something under her shawl, turned it back, and saw this ribbon, which I took from her; it was one of the pieces I had shown her - she said she had not taken it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I turn from the counter? A. You went a little way from the counter - I do not think you turned your back.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I stood at the counter, and you accused me of stealing it; I looked, and it was on the counter, under my shawl. Witness. She was about half a yard from the counter - I saw something project under her shawl, turned back her shawl, and took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-287-person2689">
                  SAMUEL 
                  PAGE
               <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2689" type="surname" value="PAGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2689" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-287-person2689" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent for, and took this ribbon from the witness - I searched her as far as decency would permit, and then Mrs. Gaze searched her, and found this other ribbion in her bosom.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to see if they could match the ribbon I had, but they had none - I deferred having any.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
